    • Constructor Detail

      • Compound

        public Compound(java.lang.String auxName,
        int auxNChains,
        double auxMObs,
        double auxRefKMD,
        int auxMinC,
        int auxMaxC)
        Generates a "Compound" object for matching and calculation algorithms in RKMD; the parameters are typically loaded from an algorithm which reads a database file.
        Parameters:
        auxName - Compound name; it is best practice to include the class, subclass and adduct as the name, and delimit this hierarchy by semicolons. Example: name="class;subclass;adduct"
        auxNChains - Number of chains
        auxMObs - Reference mass for the compound
        auxRefKMD - Reference mass for the compoun
        auxMinC - Minimum number of allowable carbon-atoms in the compound
        auxMaxC - Maximum number of allowable carbon-atoms in the compound

      • inRange

        public boolean inRange(double auxCNo)
        Determines if a given value (auxCNo) falls between the minimum and maximum number of carbon atoms for this compound.

        The equality is inclusive: i.e. inRange(x) returns TRUE if minC <= x <= maxC

        Parameters:
        auxCNo - the input value to test
